,12,21,31,59,74,16,37,37,57,106,136,166,74,125,204,257,288,383,393,248,235,808,686,716,818,937,477,366,1033,874,840,800,932,455,288,394<!--Please use the raw data and not the numbers in daily reports-->\n|y2=6,4,2,5,2,9,5,7,12,13,17,37,39,30,27,61,24,58,55,70,44,65,116,122,142,149,186,147,93,138,178,145,153,154,93,64,32<!--Please use the raw data and not the numbers in daily reports-->\n|y3=2,1,13,12,20,23,6,19,42,22,46,69,113,66,53,115,127,185,246,189,164,176,394,378,325,375,371,206,213,533,581,444,451,469,221,184,210<!--Please use the raw data and not the numbers in daily reports-->\n|y4=0,0,0,6,0,1,0,1,3,7,1,5,19,7,10,8,10,5,32,11,14,13,13,8,12,15,25,13,13,27,18,23,12,19,14,9,3<!--Please use the raw data and not the numbers in daily reports-->\n}}\n\n<div style=\"height:30px;display:block;\"> </div>\n'''Logistic growth models'''\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-break}}\n[[File:SARS-CoV-2 pandemic in Belgium - Semi-log.jpg|thumb|centre|500 px|[[Semi-log plot|Semi-logarithmic graph]] of the number of confirmed cases, hospitalisations, intensive care cases and deaths in Belgium as of 2020-04-08]]\n{{col-break}}\n[[File:SARS-CoV-2 pandemic in Belgium - Linear.jpg|thumb|centre|500 px|Graph of the number of daily increase of confirmed cases, hospitalisations, intensive care cases and deaths in Belgium as of 2020-04-08]]\n{{col-end}}\n{{clear}}\n[[File:20200406 Logistic growth COVID-19 Belgium.png|thumb|centre|500 px|[[Logistic function|Logistic growth model]] fit for hospitalised COVID-19 cases in Belgium for data  (see table above for data used)  from 15/03/2020 until 06/04/2020. The exponential phases have a growth/decline rate of 25.9% and the total number of cumulated hospitalised cases stabilises at 10515. Beyond 6 April the curves shown are only a trend according to the logistic growth model, these have an uncertainty range associated to them and should not be seen as a prediction.]]\n\n==See also==\n*[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in France]] \n*[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Netherlands]]\n\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|Belgium|Medicine|Viruses}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=\"nb\"}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.info-coronavirus.be/en/ www.info-coronavirus.be], information website from the Belgian government\n* [https://epidemio.wiv-isp.be/ID/Pages/2019-nCoV.aspx New Coronavirus (Disease: COVID-19, Virus: SARS-CoV-2)], epidemiological updates in Belgium - [[Sciensano]]\n* [https://epistat.wiv-isp.be/Covid/ EPISTAT- Infectious Diseases Data Explorations & Visualizations], raw data of the pandemic in Belgium  - [[Sciensano]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{2019\u20132020 coronavirus pandemic}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Belgium| ]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Belgium]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|Belgium]]\n[[Category:2020 in Belgium|Coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Belgium]]\n", "name_user": "Jrm7", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eMarch 2020 \u2013 Spread:typo", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Belgium"}
{"title_page": "Bruce Dellis", "text_new": "{{BLP sources|date=July 2010}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Bruce Dellis\n| image              =\n| caption            = Dellis on the set of Raising Buchanan\n| birth_name         = Bruce Dellis\n| home_town           = [[Tempe, Arizona]], U.S.\n| occupation         = Film director and screenwriter\n| years_active       = 2003\u2013present\n| spouse             = {{marriage|Connie Dellis|1990}}\n| children           = 1\n}}\n\n'''Bruce Dellis''' is an American [[film director]] and [[screenwriter]] based in [[Tempe, Arizona|Tempe]], AZ. He has written and directed several award-winning short films and features.\n\n==Career==\nIn 2006, Dellis won two [[Rocky Mountain Emmy Awards]] for ''The Intervention of Brad''.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.ifp.org/ifpnews/newsitem.php?id=514 | title=IFP/PHX's Screen Wars has been Awarded Four Emmys | publisher=IFP | date=October 10, 2006 | accessdate=20 January 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070222003238/http://www.ifp.org/ifpnews/newsitem.php?id=514 | archive-date=February 22, 2007}}</ref> That same year, he was named Arizona Filmmaker of the Year by the Phoenix Film Foundation.\n\nIn 2007, he wrote the feature-length film ''[[Netherbeast Incorporated]]'', which premiered at the 2007 AFI/Dallas Film Festival. The offbeat comedy stars [[Darrell Hammond]], [[Judd Nelson]], [[Robert Wagner]], [[Jason Mewes]], [[Dave Foley]], [[Steve Burns]], and [[Amy Davidson]].\n\nDellis won two more Rocky Mountain Emmy Awards in 2008 for his offbeat short film on the [[Parent-Teacher Association|PTA]] called ''Fuller PTA: Better Than Stepping on a Rusty Nail''.\n\nIn all, Dellis has been nominated for a total of 14 Rocky Mountain Emmys, winning five.\n\nDellis wrote and directed a chapter of the anthology film ''[[Locker 13]]''. The chapter, titled \"The Benevolent Byzantine Order of the Nobles of the Enigmatic Oracle\", stars [[David Huddleston]], [[Bart Johnson]], and [[Curtis Armstrong]]. Locker 13 was released in 2014.\n\nIn 2019, Dellis wrote and directed \"Raising Buchanan,\" a feature film starring [[Ren\u00e9 Auberjonois]], Amanda Melby, [[M. Emmet Walsh]], Cathy Shim, Terence Bernie Hines, and [[Robert Ben Garant]]. It concerns a woman who steals the body of President [[James Buchanan]] with the hope of ransoming him for a large payoff, but finds that no one is particularly interested in getting him back. The film has won several awards on the film festival circuit.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.phoenixfilmfestival.com/awards | title=2019 Phoenix Film Festival award winners | publisher=Phx Film Fest | accessdate=18 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.manhattanff.com/awards | title=2019 Manhattan Film Festival award winners | publisher=Manhattan Film Festival | accessdate=18 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n=== Films ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Director\n! Writer\n! Producer\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Raising Buchanan]]''<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt7304026 | title=Raising Buchanan | publisher=IMDB | accessdate=18 July 2019}}</ref>\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n|\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Locker 13]]''<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1241226 | title=Locker 13 | publisher=IMDB | accessdate=18 July 2019}}</ref>\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n|\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[The Benevolent Byzantine Order of the Nobles of the Enigmatic Oracle]]''<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1837672 | title=The Benevolent Byzantine Order of the Nobles of the Enigmatic Oracle | publisher=IMDB | accessdate=18 July 2019}}</ref>\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n|\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''Cocktail Wizard''<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1391542 | title=Cocktail Wizard | publisher=IMDB | accessdate=18 July 2019}}</ref>\n|\n| {{yes}}\n|\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''Fuller PTA: Better Than Stepping on a Rusty Nail!''<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1843159 | title=