{"title_page": "Noosphere Ventures", "text_new": "{{Infobox company\n| name                = Noosphere Ventures\n| logo                = [[Image:Noosphere_Ventures.png]]\n| industry            = [[Space]]\n| founded             = 2014\n| founder             = [[Max Polyakov]] - Managing Partner\n| website             = [https://noosphereventures.com noosphereventures.com]\n}}\n\nNoosphere Ventures - NOOSPHERE VENTURE PARTNERS LP is a space-focused investment firm.\n\n== ABOUT ==\nFounded on 4 June 2014 by [[Max Polyakov]], the firm makes [[Venture capital|venture]] and traditional investments. Headquartered in the USA, [[Menlo Park, California]], Noosphere Ventures invests in projects from all over the world mainly focused on space and development of a New Space concept as well as in underperforming businesses. Noosphere Ventures developed the ecosystems of Space-technology.\n\nThe Noosphere space portfolio also includes projects EOS Data Analytics, including EOS SAR; Firefly Aerospace; D-Orbit; Space systems engineering, who is the owner of Space Electric Thruster Systems (SETS), etc.\n\n==== Key people ====\n[[Max Polyakov]] - Managing Partner\n\nMark Watt - Consultant\n\nWilliam Woods - Space Entrepreneur consultant\n\nEvgeniy Yakovlev - VP of space business development\n\n== STRATEGIC VISION ==\nStrategic development and expansion in the space sector are one of the primary focus areas of Noosphere Ventures. The company\u00a0 believes that the space industry will adopt the principles of vertical integration, allowing the new generation of space companies to hold control over the launch, satellites, data analysis, communications, and ground stations.\n\nBy versing funds into the development of game-changing space initiatives, we are on the cusp of creating a next-gen business vertical that is to bring about fundamental planet wide changes.\n\n== INVESTMENT TARGETS ==\n\n\nCurrent investment segments of the space ecosystem: \n\n* Orbital transfer vehicles for deploying satellites\n* Space tugs and debris removal systems\n* Component suppliers for small satellites\n* Earth observation and data analysis\n* Ground and communication services\n* Moon projects and commercial deep space exploration missions\n\n== PORTFOLIO ==\nNoosphere, as an investor and a holding company, has invested in 17 currently active companies, though not all of them are in the space industry. Noosphere has averaged between $30 million and $50 million in merger and acquisition-type investments over the past five years. In a best-case scenario, an investment in a small-satellite manufacturer or component supplier could happen by this spring.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://spacenews.com/firefly-investor-noosphere-ventures-eyes-satellite-manufacturing-sector/|title=Firefly investor Noosphere Ventures eyes satellite manufacturing sector|date=2019-01-08|website=SpaceNews.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n\nJanuary 2015 \u2013 EOS Data Analytics Inc. (EOS) added to the space portfolio company of Noosphere Ventures.\n\nMarch 2017 - Noosphere Ventures Partners' subsidiary purchased the assets, patents and intellectual property of Firefly Systems Inc. After the deal, it was renamed Firefly Aerospace. The company, with its Headquarters in Cedar Park, Texas, develops new, small satellite launch vehicles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://spacenews.com/firefly-space-systems-assets-to-be-sold/|title=Firefly Space Systems assets to be sold|date=2017-03-15|website=SpaceNews.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2019/2/22/18234604/firefly-aerospace-cape-canaveral-florida-launch-site-slc-20|title=Resurrected Firefly Aerospace will take over a launch site at busy Florida spaceport|last=Grush|first=Loren|date=2019-02-22|website=The Verge|language=en|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://arstechnica.com/science/2019/02/firefly-returns-from-the-dead-with-a-larger-rocket-and-lunar-aspirations/|title=After a remarkable resurrection, Firefly may reach space in 2019|last=Berger|first=Eric|date=2019-02-11|website=Ars Technica|language=en-us|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://medium.com/@eos_da/iaf-welcomes-its-new-member-eos-managed-by-max-polyakov-11b404ed611b|title=IAF Welcomes EOS, Managed by Max Polyakov, as New Member|last=EOS|date=2018-02-20|website=Medium|language=en|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2017, at the International Astronautical Congress (IAC) in Australia, EOS was accepted as a new member of the largest space network, the International Astronautical Federation (IAF).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wonderfulengineering.com/max-polyakovs-maxim-polyakov-eos-look-inside/|title=Max Polyakov\u2019s (Maxim Polyakov) EOS: A Look Inside|last=Admin|date=2018-04-27|website=Wonderful Engineering|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://medium.com/@eos_da/iaf-welcomes-its-new-member-eos-managed-by-max-polyakov-11b404ed611b|title=IAF Welcomes EOS, Managed by Max Polyakov, as New Member|last=EOS|date=2018-02-20|website=Medium|language=en|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n\nMarch 2019 - Firefly may carry Italian satellites D-Orbit to space on future rocket flights.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/austin/news/2019/03/04/firefly-may-carry-italian-satellites-to-space-on.html|website=www.bizjournals.com|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n\nOctober 2019\u00a0 EOS Data Analytics unveiled EOS SAR \u2013 a project to develop its own synthetic aperture radar (SAR) sensors intended for deployment in a constellation of microsatellites. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://spacenews.com/noosphere-venture-campaign-begins-coming-together-with-radar-constellation/|title=Noosphere Venture campaign begins coming together with radar constellation|date=2019-10-22|website=SpaceNews.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n\nDecember 2019 - Noosphere Ventures invests in D-Orbit Series C.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://spacenews.com/seraphim-noosphere-d-orbit/|title=Seraphim Capital, Noosphere Ventures invest in D-Orbit|date=2019-12-20|website=SpaceNews.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.startupbusiness.it/nuovo-round-per-d-orbit-e-lancio-previsto-a-marzo-2020/102807/|title=New space, nuovo round per D-Orbit e lancio previsto a marzo 2020|date=2019-12-16|website=Startup Business|language=it|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n\n==== Non space projects ====\nFrom 2014 to 2017, the found did not focus on space projects but invested in technology projects.\n\n22 May 2016 - Noosphere invested in Thync. Series B round of investments.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbinsights.com/investor/noosphere-ventures|title=Noosphere Ventures - CB Insights|website=www.cbinsights.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://noosphereventures.com/thync-big/|title=Thync Big|website=noosphereventures.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n\n15 May 2017 -\u00a0 Noosphere invested in Yola.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://uprom.info/news/ekonomika/biznes/amerikanskiy-konstruktor-saytiv-yola-vidkriv-r-amp-d-tsentr-v-ukrayini/|title=\u0410\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0438\u043a\u0430\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043a\u043e\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0443\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u0441\u0430\u0439\u0442\u0456\u0432 Yola \u0432\u0456\u0434\u043a\u0440\u0438\u0432 R&D-\u0446\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0440 \u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0456|date=2017-05-28|language=uk|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n\n'''Noosphere Venture also has minor investments:''' PocketGuard<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pitchbook.com/profiles/company/104678-29|title=PocketGuard Company Profile: Valuation & Investors {{!}} PitchBook|website=pitchbook.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>, Kangaroo Health, Circle Medical<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.techprevue.com/max-polyakov-judges-medical-startup-competition/|title=Max Polyakov to be One of the Judges of Medical Startup Competition|last=Prajapati|first=Vinay|date=2018-03-27|website=TechPrevue|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>, Aquila<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://innovationhouse.org.ua/en/statti/maksym-polyakov-medytsyna-budushhego-v-novyh-obemah-dannyh/|title=Max Polyakov: new big data is the medicine of the future|date=2018-02-20|website=Innovation House|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>.\n\n== PHILOSOPHY ==\nThe philosophy of the noosphere is based on the theory of Vladimir Vernadsky, who defined the noosphere as \"the sphere of human thinking.\" The goal is to use knowledge as a fundamental creative force that affects the entire biosphere as a whole.\n\nIt was the theory about Vernadsky\u2019s noosphere that formed the basis of the logo and organization name.\n\n== ANALYTICS ==\n'''Noosphere makes quarterly reports and market analysis about Venture Investments In Space Industry:'''\n\n[https://noosphereventures.com/venture-investments-in-space-industry-q1-2019-report-2/ Q1 2019 Report]\n\n[https://noosphereventures.com/q2-2019-edition-of-venture-investments-in-space-industry/ Q2 2019 Report]\n\n[https://noosphereventures.com/q3-2019-edition-of-venture-investments-in-space-industry/ Q3 2019 Report]\n\n[https://noosphereventures.com/q4-2019-edition-of-venture-investments-in-space-market/ Q4 2019 Report]\n<references />\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox company\n| name                = Noosphere Ventures\n| logo                = [[Image:Noosphere_Ventures.png]]\n| industry            = [[Space]]\n| founded             = 2014\n| founder             = [[Max Polyakov]] - Managing Partner\n| website             = [https://noosphereventures.com noosphereventures.com]\n}}\n\nNoosphere Ventures - NOOSPHERE VENTURE PARTNERS LP is a space-focused investment firm.\n\n== ABOUT ==\nFounded on 4 June 2014 by Max Polyakov, the firm makes venture and traditional investments. Headquartered in the USA, [[Menlo Park, California]], Noosphere Ventu